result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (1st w/ Passenger < 16 Yrs Old) and Operating w/ PAC-Passenger < 16 Yrs, PAC>=0.08, <0.15 (1st). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (1st w/ Passenger < 16 Yrs Old) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC-Passenger < 16 Yrs, PAC>=0.08, <0.15 (1st) was dismissed by the court.

  • Jose Angel Hernandez Jr was found guilty of OWI (1st w/ Passenger < 16 Yrs Old), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).
  • Jose Angel Hernandez Jr was found guilty of Possession of THC, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

records.addlTxt: 2:17 pm cases called. 15CM193, 15TR1153, 15TR1154, 15TR1555, 15TR1156, 15TR1157, 15TR1158, & 15TR1159. Defendant Jose Angel Hernandez in court with attorney Jeanne L. Zamzow.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Agreement stated on the record by ADA Anderson. Attorney Zamzow concurs.   Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed.  Plea: No Contest to Count 1 & Count 4 & 15TR1155.  Court accepts plea and enters JOC. Court dismisses outright Count 2 & Count 3 and dismisses and reads-in Count 5, & 15TR1153, 15TR1154, 15TR1556, 15TR1557, 15TR1558 & 15TR1559 and an uncharged read-in of bailjumping from 8/21/2015. Court sentences the defendant to: Count 1-90 days WCJ, with Huber and Good Time Credit. No credit for time served. To begin serving no later than January 2, 2016. $1560.00 fine inclusive of costs, 12 mo IID effective today, 15 mo DL revocation. OWI Assessment. COUNT 4- 90 days WCJ, concurrent to Count 1. Costs to be paid within 60 days. DNA sample & surcharge. Bond to be applied. 15TR1155-$200.50 to be paid within 60 days or payment plan.  Appeal Rights Given.

NOT PUT OF RECORD: Attorney Jeanne L. Zamzow in court appears telephonically.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Atty Zamzow requesting a plea/sentencing hearing.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for November 4, 2015 at 02:15 pm.

NOT PUT OF RECORD: Attorney Jeanne L. Zamzow in court.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Atty Zamzow requesting another STC.  Status conference scheduled for October 1, 2015 at 02:50 pm.

The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician.    No operation of any motor vehicles without a valid driver's license.

Cases Called @ 3:00 PM with all pending civil citations: Defendant Jose Angel Hernandez in court.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Complaint Stated - Advised of offense and minimum/maximum penalty.  Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived.  Advised of right of Counsel.  Def wants counsel - employed.  Def states he will retain his own counsel.  Court does not believe based upon earnings that he will qualify for SPD services.  Court will proceed with the understanding that he will retain his own counsel.  NGP entered by Court as to all matters.   STC Scheduled - NOH Given.  Court enters Riverside Ruling in favor of the State and probable cause finding as to each count alleged within the complaint.  Status conference scheduled for September 1, 2015 at 01:55 pm.
